habitat_description: Primary habitat for the Chuska Mountain chipmunk can be characterized as moderately to steeply sloping terrain vegetated with ponderosa pine, Douglas-fir, Gambel oak, and aspen above 2700 meters. They can also be found in areas with sandstone ledges, sometimes in wooded areas with logs and slash  (Sullivan and Petersen 1988).
